  "id": "ex_technical_c8ae50b7",
  "intent": "Execute a bacterial lysis and PCR prep protocol for Listeria and Salmonella detection. First, prepare lysis buffers by adding 500\u00b5L of specific enzymes to designated buffer tubes with 10x mixing cycles at 200\u00b5L volume. Distribute 70\u00b5L lysis buffer to Listeria wells and 90\u00b5L to Salmonella wells in a temperature-controlled aluminum block. Transfer 30\u00b5L Listeria samples and 10\u00b5L Salmonella samples to respective lysis wells, mixing 3x at 50\u00b5L and 18\u00b5L volumes. Incubate at 37\u00b0C for 20 minutes, then 95\u00b0C for 10 minutes. Finally, transfer 5\u00b5L processed samples to PCR plate wells and add positive controls to designated positions.",
